cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 125 miles N of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to slow, meander in the SE Gulf, then turn north and move toward the NE Gulf Coast late week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend / northeast Gulf Coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical-storm watch in effect for western Cuba (La Habana, Artemisa, Mayabeque, Pinar del Rio and Isle of Youth)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Keys, southern and central Florida peninsula, Bahamas, and eventually the northeast Gulf Coast
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible late week; tropical-storm-force winds unlikely (≤3% chance)
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected at the Virginia coast from Eta
weather_observation.rainfall: Light to locally moderate rain possible 14–15 Nov as Eta’s remnants pass well south; totals below damaging thresholds
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor coastal rip-current enhancement possible, otherwise none
